      "text": [
        " «عَلَيْهِ بَقَرَةٌ يَذْبَحُهَا وَ يَطُوفُ شَوْطاً آخَرَ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2849 - Abu Abdullah (as) was asked about a man who performed six circuits (Ashwat) between Safa and Marwah, thinking they were seven, and later, after having become lawful (Halal) and engaging in relations with women, realized that he had only completed six.\nImam (as) said: \"He must sacrifice a cow and complete one more circuit (Shawt).\""
        ]
      }
    },
